==English==
===Etymology===
From ''un-'' + ''load''

===Transitive verb===
'''unload'''
#take off or remove the load from something
#discharge the cargo of a ship
#discharge or pour a liquid
#give vent to or express
#get rid of or dispose
#deliver something forcefully

===Intransitive verb===
'''unload'''
#take off its load
#discharge its cargo
#confide in someone

